  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Those who was with him up to the road there, where Israel was supposed to be-- the future-- finished.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They went back to-- to the sky, and down came another set, which they-- they walked with him further.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But this is just a legend.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The actual meaning is that there were people-- they will say, you are-- if you are on the ground, but your head could reach up to the sky if you are up to it and if you make it this way.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "These people that were teaching there-- these people in this-- they were real scholars and dedicated.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we used to call them 'der himmelmenschen'-- [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It means they were-- you look to you like a normal human being, but their-- their mind, their heads, reached to the skies.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So those were-- those were people who were dedicated to you like-- like your own family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so, between the-- the-- the friends that you made and the teachers, they were just like your own family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, no!",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was a youngster, then!",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- I came to this Ostrowca when I was-- in '35, how old was I? 15 years old.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] [SIGHS] And when the Germans came in, when-- when-- when the German occupation started in-- in 1939, I was not even 20 yet.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Just [INAUDIBLE] 20th birthday.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was alone, and I-- I became friends with some people in the city, which, on the holidays, they used-- they used to invite me for a meal or a special [INAUDIBLE] in school it was-- you know, the food was not exactly connoisseur, you know, the best food around.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So those people used to sometimes take a youngster and give him a good meal for-- for the holidays.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
